parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the catalytic converter can cause the vehicle to stall, and in extreme cases, lead to a vehicle fire, resulting in damage to the vehicle and potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
the engine shuts off
a strong acrid smell is present
smoke is visible
hot liquid is pouring into the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine booster pump can cause a fire in the engine compartment, leading to damage to the vehicle and potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: A strong acrid smell is present
hot liquid is pouring into the vehicle
smoke is visible.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rust and leaks in the oil pan can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing engine failure, which can lead to accidents or strand the driver.
symptoms: Oil leaks from the oil pan
rust is visible on the oil pan.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fire starting from the ignition wire can cause significant damage to the vehicle and potentially harm occupants, leading to a risk of injury or even fatalities.
symptoms: Smoke or flames emanating from the ignition area
burning smell
stuck ignition switch
fire under the dash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A shorted wiring harness connection to the alternator can cause an electrical fire, leading to a risk of injury or fatalities, as well as damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Alternator failure
electrical issues
burning smell
smoke or flames emanating from the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the dual fuel tank system can cause fuel to be pushed out of the top of one tank when both tanks are full, leading to fuel spills and potential fires. The popping noise when the tank is full can also indicate a pressure buildup, which can lead to tank rupture or other safety issues.
symptoms: Fuel is pushed out of the top of one tank when both tanks are full
a popping noise is heard when the tank is full
fuel spills or leaks from the tank area.
